<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-09-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">339.3921L96/17</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-08"><hi rend="italic">September 8,
                                        1920</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I am in receipt of
                                your favor of September 2nd with reference to the case of Fabio
                                Fiallo and Amerigo Lugo. The following cablegram has been sent to
                                Rear Admiral Thomas Snowden, Military Governor of Santo Domingo:
                                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Suspend all proceedings with reference to men who have been
                                        arrested for alleged revolutionary tendencies until you hear
                                        from me, and suspend sentences pending approval in
                                        Washington. Mail full reports with findings for action
                                        here.”</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <p>Will not this meet the situation?</p>
                            <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Josephus
                                Daniels</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>